a>0
\int_{0}^{\infty}\dfrac{\sin(t)}{e^{at}-1}=\sum_{0}^{\infty}\dfrac{1}{a^2n^2+1}
\dfrac{\sin(t)}{e^{at}-1}
\int_{0}^{\infty}\dfrac{\sin(t)}{e^{at}-1}
a\rightarrow \infty
\dfrac{1}{n^2a^2+1}\sim \dfrac{1}{a^2n^2}
\int_{0}^{\infty}\dfrac{\sin(t)}{e^{at}-1}\sim \sum_{0}^{\infty}\dfrac{1}{a^2n^2}=\dfrac{\pi^2}{6a^2}
{1\over e^{at} - 1} = {e^{-at} \over 1 - e^{-at}} = \sum_{n=1}^\infty e^{-ant}.
